The Punisher has been on everyone's mind from the day he made his coming book debut in the 1970's since then there have been many adaptions of the character, in both live-action and animation. Today we review the only Punisher film to not get a theatrical release, The Punisher (1989) starring Dolph Lundgren. Boy, there is A LOT to say about this relic from a bygone era of comic book movies. Did we like it? Does It hold up? You'll just have to tune in and find out! Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

